
Instance variable:
* Each instance of the class (object) contains its own separate copy of the instance variable;
this contrasts with a static variable.
* Declared in the class, outside any method or constructor.
* Can have default values and access modifiers.
* Can be declared before or after its use in the class.


Local variable:
* Declared inside a method or constructor.
* Can have default values and access modifiers.
* Must be declared before its use.